column5: We leave in 3 days, wondering there are any recent reports from groups getting off the water this weekend?
I'm sure there pounding them north of nakina.

Here is a report from last week, just north west of Nakina Just got back from an incredible week of fishing Lake O'Sullivan. All I can say is WOW. What an incredible lake. We didn't count but our group of 7 had to have caught well over 500 walleye including my PB 28". A 27", multiple 25" and 26" and too many 20" -24" to count. Also a big thank you to Bob and Shelly. A well run and very clean camp. We will be back.
Thank you just what we needed.
